commentTextItems.html: well Chase's fun is over and so is the match. Swings the ball in the air towards the square leg boundary. Milne gets under the ball and takes the catch.

commentPostTextItems.html: Ireland are all out for 154, yet again in the batting has failed to spark and they lose todays game by 190 runs.
Porterfield tops scored with 48 off 50 balls, yet too many of the top order batsmen fell cheaply.
Chasing 345 was never going to be easy against this impressive New Zealand team and so it proved.
New Zealand bowled very well with all of their bowler taking wickets. Henry finishing with three of them.
With that New Zealand claim the four points for the win and with that take unassailable lead in the Tri-Series.
Unsuprisingly Tom Latham has just been named Man of the Match for his fantastic century in New Zealand's innings.
There is still one more match left in the Tri-Series when Bangladesh and New Zealand play again on Wednesday. So please join me then. This is Justin saying goodnight from Malahide.

commentTextItems.html: gets forward and the ball spins past the bat, gets hit on the pad. outside the line though
gets an inside edge through square leg
biggest cheer of the day as Chase pulls a short ball over the long-on boundary. Almost hits the scoreboard. 150 up for Ireland
